selines.\ndocs/milestones.md:153:**What should the wave model do differently than a baseline point-neuron model?**  \ndocs/milestones.md:171:* **Weak:** the surface model shows propagation or spread that the point model cannot show by construction  \ndocs/milestones.md:179:2. **`10–25 s`**: split screen with matched point baseline on the left and surface model on the right for the same T4/T5-centered circuit  \ndocs/milestones.md:269:* **readout stop point:** T4a/T5a axon terminals in lobula plate layer 1\ndocs/milestones.md:321:* promote **L1/L2/L3 point models** if the upstream delay abstraction becomes the main criticism  \ndocs/milestones.md:372:  - point-simulated  \ndocs/milestones.md:541:  - point-to-point  \ndocs/milestones.md:784:- **point neuron** — coarse functional placeholder\ndocs/milestones.md:1101:**Shared checkpoint**\ndocs/milestones.md:1123:**Shared checkpoint**\ndocs/milestones.md:1145:**Shared checkpoint**\ndocs/milestones.md:1165:**Shared checkpoint**\ndocs/milestones.md:1188:**Shared checkpoint**\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:28:- `point_neuron`\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:34:- `point_simulated` -> `point_neuron`\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:43:### `point_neuron`\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:87:  may express branch-local timing or attenuation that a point neuron cannot,\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:116:- point -> point\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:117:- point -> skeleton\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:118:- point -> surface\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:119:- skeleton -> point\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:122:- surface -> point\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:133:Promoting `point_neuron -> skeleton_neuron -> surface_neuron`, or demoting in\ndocs/hybrid_morphology_design.md:173:names or changing what `point_neuron`, `skeleton_neuron`, or `surface_neuron`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
